2.body:
In the last level we used the println() method to print out a length of text, we can put any amount of words or phrases into this method.
```java
    System.out.println("Hello World!");
    System.out.println("Java is the best Language!");    
    System.out.println("I love Pepperoni Pizza.");
```

In addition to text we can also output numbers and preform math equations
```java
    System.out.println(5 + 5);
```

we can also use print() instead of println(), this does not create a new line after every statement.

```java
    System.out.print("Hello World!");
    System.out.print(" Not a new line");
```

We also need to add a space in the beginning of the second statement, because Java wont do it for us.

